Financial Stability Oversight Council at the U.S. Treasury on July 28, 2023 in Washington, DC.&nbsp;</em> | Photo by Kevin Dietsch/Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Bt4h5N\">The US Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) adopted new <a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/securities-topics/climate-esg\">rules</a> that compel large companies to disclose their greenhouse gas emissions and tell investors how their business is affected by climate change.</p>\n<p id=\"zHfkF8\">The new rules are weaker than what the SEC initially <a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/news/press-release/2022-46\">proposed</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/21/22988921/sec-companies-greenhouse-", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/6/24092159/sec-climate-change-disclosure-rule-scope-3-emissions", "language": "en", "comments": [], "page_rating_contents": 0, "permanent": false, "page_rating": 0}, {"tags": [], "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "vote": 0, "user": null, "bookmarked": false, "thumbnail": null, "dead": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "album": "", "date_published": "2024-03-06T16:30:00+00:00", "artist": null, "age": null, "title": "Epic says its iOS game store plans are stalled because Apple banned its developer account", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of Epic Games\u2019 logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UVtcjg9ktM3_hLNeo1LQHGOW7aU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73186404/acastro_STK108__02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"I3xSG4\">Epic\u2019s plans to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/25/24050800/epic-games-store-fortnite-apple-ios-launch-eu-dma\">release its own third-party app store on iOS</a> in the EU could be in trouble after Apple terminated the developer account it planned to use. In a <a href=\"https://www.epicgames.com/site/en-U